description:
## Context
Current bd-dvd fix uses TryResurrectParent, which only resurrects the immediate parent. For deeply nested hierarchies, this might not be sufficient.

## Example Scenario
Creating child with parent "bd-abc.1.2" where:
- bd-abc exists in DB
- bd-abc.1 was deleted (missing from DB, exists in JSONL)
- bd-abc.1.2 was deleted (missing from DB, exists in JSONL)

Current fix: Only tries to resurrect "bd-abc.1.2", fails because its parent "bd-abc.1" is missing.

## Solution
Replace TryResurrectParent with TryResurrectParentChain:

```go
if count == 0 {
    // Try to resurrect entire parent chain from JSONL history (bd-dvd fix)
    // This handles deeply nested hierarchies where intermediate parents are also missing
    resurrected, err := s.TryResurrectParentChain(ctx, parentID)
    if err != nil {
        return "", fmt.Errorf("failed to resurrect parent chain for %s: %w", parentID, err)
    }
    if !resurrected {
        return "", fmt.Errorf("parent issue %s does not exist and could not be resurrected from JSONL history", parentID)
    }
}
```

## Investigation
- Check if this scenario actually happens in practice
- TryResurrectParentChain already exists (resurrection.go:174-209)
- May be overkill if users always create parents before children

